{"id": "EUVD-2022-55064", "enisaUuid": "4217f8bb-89f3-3aa9-a10e-a9e4b46cfae3", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nASoC: mediatek: Fix error handling in mt8183_da7219_max98357_dev_probe\n\nThe device_node pointer is returned by of_parse_phandle()  with refcount\nincremented. We should use of_node_put() on it when done.\n\nThis function only calls of_node_put() in the regular path.\nAnd it will cause refcount leak in error paths.\nFix this by calling of_node_put() in error handling too.", "datePublished": "2025-09-23T15:31:07", "dateUpdated": "2025-09-23T15:31:07", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9b9f6227e8d0c7c46b6d9d7b8a5c4e0536049fcf", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/28a265a1ee11febeec5ea73a804f30dcec3181ca", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49161"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49161"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.05, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "21d997b2-142e-3f89-bcbf-92cbdab37725", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "2d0fac7c-b5f4-3cfd-93e7-844844acad78", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "11c0269017b212fd47c593307d2dc3eb9713b2d0 <9b9f6227e8d0c7c46b6d9d7b8a5c4e0536049fcf"}, {"id": "65470e94-9c6a-3d49-a225-026edb40791a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.17.2"}, {"id": "b31797dc-c5f5-381e-a91f-ec1d661964f2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <28a265a1ee11febeec5ea73a804f30dcec3181ca"}, {"id": "c1e112ce-3f00-3c50-956a-ef66fa1b1189", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <9b9f6227e8d0c7c46b6d9d7b8a5c4e0536049fcf"}, {"id": "c6f30e68-f01a-36ec-9282-9eeb9b6ab3e6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.2"}, {"id": "ca2e7763-d8df-3864-ba25-864b105ddf41", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "11c0269017b212fd47c593307d2dc3eb9713b2d0 <28a265a1ee11febeec5ea73a804f30dcec3181ca"